text: On May 5, 2023, a strong earthquake hit in Ishikawa Prefecture, Japan. The maximum intensity of Shindo 6+ ==Earthquake== The earthquake occurred at 2:42 p.m. JST measuring M 6.2, at a depth of 8.7 kilometers. ==References== Category:2023 disasters in Asia Category:2020s earthquakes in Asia Category:2020s in Japan Category:Earthquakes in Japan Category:Ishikawa Prefecture Category:May 2023 events Category:2023 earthquakes
